text: t.A.T.u., or known in Russian as Тату, was a Russian pop music duet, made up of Lena Katina and Yulia Volkova. The group was formed in 1999 in Moscow. Their albums include "200 Russian "200 Po Vstrechnoy", "200 km/h in the wrong lane", "Lyudi Invalidy", "Dangerous and moving" and "Waste management". They split in 2011. ==Career== t.A.T.u. released their first single "All the Things She Said" in 2002. It reached number one in the United Kingdom. The song is about a relationship between two girls. In the music video Lena and Yulia kiss each other. ITV banned it from their show CD:UK. In 2003 t.A.T.U performed "Ne Ver', Ne Boysia" at the 2003 Eurovision Song Contest for their country Russia. They came third. t.A.T.u performed at the Sochi Winter Olympics. ==References== Category:2000s music groups Category:2010s music groups Category:Electronic music groups Category:Girl groups Category:LGBT-themed musical groups Category:Moscow Category:Musical duos Category:Musical groups disestablished in 2011 Category:Musical groups established in 1999 Category:Pop music groups Category:Rock bands Category:Russian musical groups Category:1990s establishments in Russia Category:Disestablishments in Russia
